Package: scDesign3
Type: Package
Title: An all-in-one statistical framework that generates realistic single-cell omics data and infers cell heterogeneity structure
Version: 1.0.1
Authors@R: 
    c(person("Dongyuan", "Song", , "dongyuansong@ucla.edu", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0003-1114-1215")),
    person("Qingyang", "Wang", , "qw802@g.ucla.edu",  role = c("aut"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-1051-609X")))
Maintainer: Dongyuan Song <dongyuansong@ucla.edu>
Description: scDesign3 is a unified probabilistic framework that generates realistic in silico high-dimensional single-cell omics data of various cell states, including discrete cell types, continuous trajectories, and spatial locations by learning from real datasets. This package provides a convenient one-shot function to simulate new datasets and provide AIC and BIC to help evaluate the "goodness of fit" of the reference dataset.
